******
[1] Pakistan, 1st case of 2019 confirmed - Bajaur, FATA, KP
Date: Sat 2 Feb 2019
Source: Yeni Safak [edited]
https://www.yenisafak.com/en/world/pakistan-confirms-first-polio-case-in-2019-3473506


Pakistan on Saturday [2 Feb 2019] reported its 1st polio case of 2019 from northwestern Bajaur tribal district of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province bordering with Afghanistan, an official said [FATA voted to merge with KP in May 2018 so we have referenced both - Mod.JH]. "Today the 1st polio virus case of the current year [2019] has been reported from Bajaur district, where the crippling virus paralyzed an 11-month-old child," Babar Atta, head of the polio eradication program of Pakistan, told Anadolu Agency.

Six polio cases have been reported from Bajaur in the last 3 months. In several other big cities, including Karachi, Quetta, Lahore, Peshawar, and Faisalabad, there is active polio virus circulation in the sewage, which is a big risk for our children, Atta said.

Pakistan is among 3 countries in the world, including Afghanistan and Nigeria, where polio virus still exists, and the country remains under a polio-linked travel restriction imposed by the World Health Organization (WHO). In 2014, WHO made it mandatory for all people traveling from Pakistan to carry a polio vaccination certificate.

Armed assailants belonging to militant groups have frequently targeted polio vaccinators and their security detail in several parts of Pakistan. The groups see the anti-polio campaigns as part of an elaborate anti-Muslim and Western conspiracy, and often issue death threats to vaccinators, many of whom are women, for administrating the vital vaccines to children. In April 2016, assailants gunned down 7 policemen who were providing security to polio vaccinators in the southern port city of Karachi. According to Pakistani officials, around 88 people associated with the drive have been killed across Pakistan since December 2012.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[According to the End Polio Pakistan website, the date of onset of paralysis of this case was 18 Jan 2019, making this the 1st case of polio transmitted in 2019 in Pakistan (http://www.endpolio.com.pk/polioin-pakistan/polio-cases-district-wise-2019).

The previous 2 confirmed cases in January 2019 (with dates of onset in late December 2018) were also from Bajaur district in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province. As a reminder, in last week's Global Polio Eradication Initiative update, there were reports of 10 positive environmental specimens collected since 1 Jan 2019. Only one was from Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, but it was collected in Peshawar. It's important to highlight that, as a reminder, there was evidence of widespread circulation of the wild poliovirus in Pakistan.

It's also worthwhile to note that 88 people associated with the polio vaccination effort have been killed since 2012. A very sad state of affairs.

A map of the FATA districts can be found at: http://www.understandingfata.org/uf-volume-iv/images/fata-map.jpg. Bajaur is the most northerly district of the FATA, to the northeast of Jalalabad and the east of Asadabad. - Mod.MPP

