[I've included the media report on the realities faced by the 1st responders in the war against polio in Pakistan (and probably also Afghanistan), especially for the female workers. These women have been risking their lives and working in the face of adversity to achieve the goal of polio eradication in Pakistan.

It is also noteworthy to highlight the effort Rotary International continues to exert to reach the goal of polio eradication. They all (the polio 1st responders and the Rotary International volunteers) deserve our respect and admiration for the work they do. - Mod.MPP]
